<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: TOPIC: Should some human NPC guard posts be removed?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Gray Rage (DB)">Gray Rage (DB)</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:25 a.m. 31/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: TOPIC: Should some human NPC guard posts be removed?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1825" TARGET=_self>TOPIC: Should some human NPC guard posts be rremoved?</A> (TheBlack)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> I would like to hear sound arguments from the rest of you as to

<BR>&gt; why these guards should or should not be removed. My personal
<BR>&gt; feeling at this time is that at least some of these guards
<BR>&gt; should be taken out of the PvP server. In certain regions they
<BR>&gt; may be needed to protect low level players. One area that comes
<BR>&gt; to mind is the Dwarven zone around Kaladim that features a
<BR>&gt; number of scattered guard posts. At least some of these posts,
<BR>&gt; especially those allowing access to the docks and leading to
<BR>&gt; Kaladim city, need to remain to allow for traffic to flow to and
<BR>&gt; from the dock areas.
<P>&gt; Please comment on specific NPC guards, the zones they are found
<BR>&gt; in, and whether or not you think they should be removed.
<P>Admitedly I am unfamiliar with many of the guarded zones, but I do believe they surely should remain in the neighboring zone of a specific Race (Neriak-Nektulos Forest). Not sure why the Humans get guards in East Commons (accept that it seem the zone is being settled by Humans), but they are sorta difficult at times when in a mixed fight. For example: After the Humans fled the fight a guard did wade into our ranks and take out a few of our number scattering the rest of us. Surely that would have been disastrous had it happened sooner. Maybe their guards could be adjusted according to the outlying zone? The Guards in E Commons then for the Humans would be 8th 12 level and would give us Dark Elves another 'monster' to kill and give the Humans some support as well in some areas.
<P>-Gray
<P>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
